  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Preschool Spanish Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Plan and deliver engaging Spanish lessons that foster language acquisition and communication skills in young learners, while collaborating with lead teachers to monitor progress and maintain a safe, inclusive learning environment.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Design and deliver Spanish lessons tailored to young learners to maximize language exposure and engagement</li><li>Incorporate songs, stories, games, and interactive activities to enhance lesson effectiveness and learner participation</li><li>Monitor learner engagement during lessons and provide clear progress updates to lead teachers to support continuous improvement</li><li>Foster a playful, safe, and inclusive classroom environment that encourages active participation and language development</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Native Spanish speaker with demonstrated ability to teach Spanish effectively</li><li>Experience teaching early years learners to support age-appropriate lesson planning and delivery</li><li>Creativity in developing and adapting lesson content using diverse teaching methods</li><li>Effective communication skills to engage children and collaborate with staff</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Frequency: Twice a week, 1 hour per session</li><li>Compensation: $50 - $70/hour</li></ul>",
